45:37.067 --> 45:41.113
do the same thing at the top of the month
so it goes down for the--

45:41.613 --> 45:44.867
<i>Okay. Kid, you just can't give</i>
<i>somebody that kind of money.</i>

45:44.950 --> 45:45.909
<i>You can't.</i>

45:45.993 --> 45:48.370
<i>You have to report</i>
<i>something like this, declare it.</i>

45:48.454 --> 45:50.581
What are you talking about?
When--? Since when?

45:50.664 --> 45:53.083
I didn't-- Name another time
when I've had to do it.

45:53.167 --> 45:56.962
<i>It's the law. We get audited</i>
<i>every year for every dime you spend.</i>

46:02.009 --> 46:04.678
<i>-Kid, I've been doing this a long time.</i>

46:05.679 --> 46:09.391
<i>You give someone that kind of money,</i>
<i>it doesn't buy you what you think.</i>

46:09.475 --> 46:12.853
<i>It's a green light,</i>
<i>and they keep coming back for more.</i>

46:14.062 --> 46:17.649
<i>That kind of money,</i>
<i>it's not one last time.</i>

46:28.911 --> 46:30.370
-I hear you.
<i>-Okay.</i>

46:32.873 --> 46:35.000
-I just need to think, I need to, um...
<i>-Okay.</i>

46:37.961 --> 46:41.590
I need to think about,
you know, the whole thing.

46:41.673 --> 46:43.342
-So just hold off.
<i>-Yeah, take your time.</i>

46:43.425 --> 46:46.053
-Just hold off. Don't do shit.
<i>-Okay.</i>

46:46.136 --> 46:48.013
-Till I tell you to do it.
<i>-Okay. You got it.</i>

46:52.893 --> 46:55.562
My advice is to reopen the restaurant,

46:56.271 --> 46:58.857
you run the money through there,
and, boom, you declare it.

46:59.650 --> 47:03.362
Celebrities, they always go stupid with
their money in restaurants, it's simple.

47:04.822 --> 47:07.616
So, how are we gonna play it?

47:09.284 --> 47:10.410
I'll get you the money.

47:11.829 --> 47:14.706
I mean, but if you want me
to give you six mil,

47:14.790 --> 47:17.167
you gotta do better
than telling me it's all good.

47:17.251 --> 47:18.794
How may I ease your mind?

47:18.877 --> 47:21.421
Well, how do I know
it's not coming back on me?

47:21.505 --> 47:24.758
How do I know you haven't talked
to the world? Who else knows you're here?

47:24.842 --> 47:26.385
Who knows about this, knows about me?

47:26.468 --> 47:28.554
-I have none of these answers.
-Nobody.

47:28.637 --> 47:29.721
Except your brother.

47:30.722 --> 47:32.766
-You're just gonna have to trust me.
-No.

47:33.559 --> 47:35.894
No, that's not gonna fucking fly, man.

47:36.770 --> 47:40.065
You gotta do a much better job
of selling me than that, Ari.

47:40.816 --> 47:42.943
Okay, you gotta put my mind at ease.

47:43.026 --> 47:46.280
If you don't wanna put my mind
at ease, then maybe I keep the money.

47:46.363 --> 47:48.198
I'll take my chances with the cops.

47:48.282 --> 47:50.742
Me and you may end up
sharing a cell, for all I know.

47:50.826 --> 47:53.370
Okay, maybe we do.

47:53.453 --> 47:56.540
I'm sorry, man.
You're just not a very good actor.

47:56.623 --> 48:00.294
But I'll play with you, Hollywood.
All right? I'll play. How's this?

48:00.377 --> 48:04.923
In my line of work, someone finds out
I got my hooks into something fat,

48:05.007 --> 48:06.842
they want a piece of that action.

48:07.593 --> 48:08.760
And I don't want that.

48:09.553 --> 48:12.848
When you find gold, you don't tell
everyone where it's buried, right?

48:12.931 --> 48:14.474
You keep it all to yourself.

48:14.558 --> 48:18.186
And you, my friend,
I am going to keep all to myself.

48:18.270 --> 48:19.605
What about fucking Daphne?

48:19.688 --> 48:22.900
How are you so certain that the cops
won't find her body on their own?

48:22.983 --> 48:26.069
Because it's someplace safe
where nobody will find it.

48:26.153 --> 48:29.698
How do I know that in a month
you don't go and jack the price up on me?

48:29.781 --> 48:32.743
The minute I cash the first check,
I am your partner.

48:33.493 --> 48:35.412
-I share the same risk.
-You're my partner?

48:35.996 --> 48:39.458
Okay, so I guess that means
I gotta trust you, right?

48:46.882 --> 48:49.801
We're gonna do the, um…
we're gonna do the restaurant thing.

48:49.885 --> 48:51.053
Good.

48:51.136 --> 48:54.306
I'll put it in you and Carlton's name.
Y'all take it from there.

48:54.848 --> 48:58.226
After that, I don't wanna talk to you
no more. I don't wanna see your face.

48:58.310 --> 49:00.604
I don't wanna be associated
with you anymore.

49:00.687 --> 49:02.731
I don't know if I can do that, I mean,

49:04.274 --> 49:06.902
I kinda thought maybe
I'd be an… and actor,

49:06.985 --> 49:09.738
and maybe you could give me
a role in one of your movies.

49:09.821 --> 49:12.032
You just think
you can shit on me, don't you?

49:13.367 --> 49:15.786
You can shit all over me because
I need your fucking help,

49:15.869 --> 49:16.912
is that what you think?

49:16.995 --> 49:19.831
Kid, just take a fucking shower.

49:19.915 --> 49:23.418
Have a good shit. Stop waking up
with dead girls in your bed,

49:24.211 --> 49:25.754
and this will go away.

49:25.837 --> 49:28.590
You won't have to do this again.
Can we get on with it?

49:33.303 --> 49:35.180
How'd you get the body out of here?

49:36.056 --> 49:38.642
It's a hotel, there's cameras everywhere,
how'd you do it?

49:38.725 --> 49:40.102
I had to break some bones.

49:41.311 --> 49:44.106
Then I folded her up, into a little ball,

49:45.023 --> 49:46.942
and I stuffed her into the cart.

49:48.652 --> 49:50.946
We rolled that cart
to the service elevator.

49:52.155 --> 49:55.283
Fourth floor cameras are out,
so we went to the fourth floor and then…

49:56.493 --> 49:58.120
the trash chute's on the fourth floor,

49:58.203 --> 50:01.873
it leads down
to the Cuthbert Street Dumpster.

50:06.795 --> 50:10.924
You see, I used to have a contract
with this place, this hotel. So…

50:12.551 --> 50:15.512
And then I wrapped her in a tarp,

50:15.595 --> 50:18.515
and your brother and I,
we put her in the trunk of a car,

50:18.598 --> 50:20.934
and we went away.

50:22.227 --> 50:23.186
Okay.

50:25.188 --> 50:26.898
But I got a question for you now.

50:31.194 --> 50:32.821
How does it feel to be so rich?

50:32.904 --> 50:34.322
You're unreal, man.

50:36.033 --> 50:37.492
It's complicated.

50:37.576 --> 50:39.036
Well, I've got time.

50:40.871 --> 50:42.330
Bet you fucking do.

50:46.460 --> 50:48.712
Everything I got, I earned. That's all me.

50:50.047 --> 50:53.425
I never had my hand out,
I never took something that wasn't mine.

50:54.885 --> 50:56.136
I never hurt anybody.

50:57.262 --> 50:59.264
I took a lot of people with me.

50:59.347 --> 51:02.267
A whole lot of fucking people.
And all those people rely on me now.

51:02.350 --> 51:03.769
And now you rely on me.

51:04.686 --> 51:06.396
Being rich ain't that simple, Ari.

51:07.355 --> 51:09.357
Just like you
getting that dead body out of here,

51:09.441 --> 51:11.193
it's a lot of twists and turns.

51:12.486 --> 51:16.865
See, the funny thing about making money,
the more you make, the more you realize

51:16.948 --> 51:19.201
the money is secondary
to the decisions you make.

51:19.284 --> 51:21.578
Sorry. You really believe
that shit, right? Like…

51:21.661 --> 51:25.207
No, I'm asking because I saw you on TV,
you were doing all that motivational shit.

51:25.290 --> 51:28.001
And I thought it was
just a bunch of crap, a gimmick,

51:28.085 --> 51:30.754
but you're standing here telling me,
and you actually believe it.

51:30.837 --> 51:31.713
-I do.
-All right.

51:31.797 --> 51:35.258
When people run up on me and talk shit
and think they can get away with it,

51:35.342 --> 51:38.053
well, that's why that pisses me off.
It annoys me.

51:38.136 --> 51:40.972
It annoys the fuck out of me.
Because of what I believe, well…

51:41.056 --> 51:43.350
That's the reason
these same people can't take advantage.

51:43.433 --> 51:45.602
Will you just write the fucking check?

51:55.153 --> 51:56.154
I heard you.

51:59.491 --> 52:01.159
Write the fucking check.

52:03.578 --> 52:05.872
It's so easy to take too. Right?

52:07.374 --> 52:09.751
Everybody can just fucking take from me.

52:11.211 --> 52:14.464
-Why not? It's so fucking easy for me too.
-Uh-huh.

52:15.132 --> 52:16.883
'Cause everybody else assumes
that it's easy,

52:16.967 --> 52:20.470
but the difference between you
and everybody else is that you…

52:22.514 --> 52:23.765
you made a mistake.

52:25.517 --> 52:27.727
You told me how to get
the fucking body out!

52:29.938 --> 52:30.981
You fucker!

52:51.585 --> 52:52.419
Fuck you!

52:52.502 --> 52:53.837
-Fuck you!

52:54.462 --> 52:55.463
Fuck you!

53:01.887 --> 53:03.889
Fuck you! Huh?

53:03.972 --> 53:05.849
You wanna fucking take from me?

53:07.809 --> 53:08.810
Huh?

53:08.894 --> 53:10.729
You wanna fucking take from me?

53:11.521 --> 53:12.480
Huh?

53:14.107 --> 53:15.192
Fuck you.

53:17.402 --> 53:18.403
Fuck you.

53:23.074 --> 53:24.284
Get the fuck off me.

54:06.117 --> 54:08.286
What's up? What you doing up?
It's 2:00 a.m. there.

54:08.370 --> 54:11.581
<i>Patrick spent the night,</i>
<i>and we watched a scary movie.</i>

54:11.665 --> 54:13.458
You're not supposed to watch scary movies.

54:13.541 --> 54:15.210
<i>I know, but I did.</i>

54:15.293 --> 54:17.504
<i>Patrick's asleep, and now I'm afraid.</i>

54:17.587 --> 54:19.256
You ain't gotta be afraid, man.

54:20.257 --> 54:22.259
I told you that. Plus, the monsters, they…

54:23.635 --> 54:26.805
The monsters only come after
the people that they know are scared.

54:27.847 --> 54:29.266
<i>Are you having fun?</i>

54:37.524 --> 54:38.566
No.

54:40.652 --> 54:42.737
No, man, I'm not having fun.

54:44.656 --> 54:47.867
Why don't you go to bed, okay?
I'll call you in the morning.

54:47.951 --> 54:50.829
<i>Okay. Well, I love you.</i>

54:53.123 --> 54:54.499
I miss you.

54:54.582 --> 54:56.293
<i>-I miss you too.</i>
-Mm…

54:56.376 --> 54:57.752
<i>Go to bed, Dad.</i>

55:25.030 --> 55:26.656
What the fuck did you do?

55:31.870 --> 55:34.414
I decided that I didn't wanna pay
six million dollars.
